{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the responsibilities of COMPANY in supporting Bravatek, but lacks detail on financial contributions and potential liabilities.",
  "operative_text": "COMPANY agrees to use its best efforts to promote and support project lead finding and after-sales support of Bravatek by: a. Listing Bravatek in all appropriate sales and marketing materials as a non-exclusive alliance partner (with focus of government customers)   b. Provide timely responses to both technical and administrative questions posed by Bravatek.   c. Promote Bravatek's product and service offerings whenever possible.   d. Aid Bravatek in the writing of any technical/marketing/sales documents when requested and participate in mutually-agreed upon sales calls.   e. Provide Bravatek with co-branded marketing material that can be emailed or handed to prospective clients.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause lacks detail on financial contributions and potential liabilities for COMPANY's support of Bravatek, which could lead to ambiguity regarding the scope of responsibility and potential risks.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["COMPANY"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the joint development and marketing responsibilities of the JV partners, but lacks clarity on financial obligations and risk allocation.",
  "operative_text": "Bravatek and COMPANY agree to jointly: a. Develop and implement a joint Product Solution and Application Strategy whereby targeted markets/potential client- types/applications are mutually agreed upon; b. Support each other in all agreed-upon technical, marketing and promotional efforts; c. Develop a joint strategy for developing new product/services/capabilities to mutually benefit both parties; d. Utilize each other as Preferred Vendors for services whenever possible upon mutual agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on financial obligations and risk allocation, particularly regarding capital calls, funding mechanisms, and liability in case of default or insolvency.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Bravatek", "COMPANY"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause lacks clarity on the mechanics of capital calls, particularly in the event a participant cannot fund their share. This could lead to dilution and financial instability for the non-operator.",
  "operative_text": "When custom Products are designed, developed and to be delivered to Bravatek-identified perspective clients, the parties shall agree to a proposed sales price for use during the project in writing prior to the commencement of each project. For any Product or Solution sold to any perspective clients introduced by Bravatek registered with COMPANY via email to COMPANY's CEO and delivered through Bravatek or a COMPANY-designated distribution affiliate(s) or sales channel(s), Bravatek will receive a lead-finder fee, to be mutually discussed and finally decided by COMPANY at the range of minimum of 10% to maximum of 20% of project revenue, with an exact fee to be depending upon the overall project sales margin and cost of development and delivery of each project, payable NET 30 days after each client payment on delivered products received at COMPANY's bank account.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how capital calls will be handled in the event a participant cannot fund their share. This could lead to dilution and financial instability for the non-operator.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 4"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines confidential information and outlines non-disclosure obligations for the parties involved in the joint venture. It's important to ensure clarity on how 'publicly available' information is defined, as this could impact future disclosures.",
  "operative_text": "‘Confidential Information’ shall mean any and all technical and non-technical information, documents and materials related to client projects of party and products, services and business of each of the parties. COMPANY and Bravatek agree to maintain in strict confidence and not to disclose or disseminate, or to use for any purposes other than performance of the projects, the Confidential Information disclosed.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The definition of 'Confidential Information' is broad and could lead to disputes regarding what constitutes confidential information. Clarify how publicly available information is defined and how it will be handled in the context of this joint venture.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Confidential Information"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines confidentiality obligations for a period of five years after termination, but does not address potential risks to the non-operator's financial stability or rights.",
  "operative_text": "For a period of five (5) years after termination of this Agreement, the parties shall treat as confidential all information and take every reasonable precaution and use all reasonable efforts to prevent the unauthorized disclosure of the same. The parties agree to take all steps reasonably necessary and appropriate to ensure that their employees, agents, and/or assistants treat all information as confidential and to ensure that such employees, agents, and/or assistants are familiar with and abide by the terms of this Agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause does not address potential risks to the non-operator's financial stability or rights in case of a breach of confidentiality. ",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["5 years", "parties"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines a standard twelve-month term with automatic renewal, and the ability to terminate by either party after ninety days' notice.",
  "operative_text": "The term of this Agreement is twelve (12) months from the date hereof, and will be automatically renewed for one (1) additional twelve month period unless either party shall notify the other in writing of its intention not to renew. Such notice must be given ninety (90) days prior to expiration of the original term. This Agreement may also be terminated by either party upon ninety (90) days written notice.",
